The paper deals with the problem of multi-agent consensus in the presence of faults/attacks, which is a topic in the field of control systems (cs.SY). The use of mean subsequence reduced (MSR) algorithms, which are commonly studied in computer science, suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of randomization, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and networking (cs.NI). Finally, the paper deals with quantization, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
